In this example, we set the rich text content of the document to a single line string using HTML formatting. We set the color of the text to red using the `<font>` tag. We then used the setHtml() method to set the content of the QTextDocument. The toPlainText() method can also be used to retrieve the plain text content of the document.

To display a QTextDocument with rich text content that is limited to a single line in a QLabel widget, you can set the text format to rich text using the setTextFormat() method, and set the text using the setText() method. Here is an example:

```
#include <QApplication>
#include <QLabel>
#include <QTextDocument>

